endance = 35,000\n|referee =  Andries Van Leeuwen ([[Netherlands|NED]])\n}}\nAEK Athens become the champions due to the better total goal average.\n\n==Top goalscorers==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!Rank\n!Player\n!Club\n!Goals\n|-\n!1\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Greece|old}} [[Kostas Nestoridis]]\n|align=\"left\"|[[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]]\n|23\n|-\n!2\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Greece|old}} [[Vangelis Panakis]]\n|align=\"left\"|[[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]]\n|21\n|-\n!3\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Greece|old}} [[Giorgos Sideris]]\n|align=\"left\"|[[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]]\n|18\n|-\n!4\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Greece|old}} [[Mimis Papaioannou]]\n|align=\"left\"|[[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]]\n|17\n|-\n!5\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Greece|old}} [[Andreas Papaemmanouil]]\n|align=\"left\"|[[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]]\n|15\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|6\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Greece|old}} [[Andreas Antonatos]]\n|align=\"left\"|[[Ethnikos Piraeus F.C.|Ethnikos Piraeus]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|14\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|Greece|old}} [[Stelios Psychos]]\n|align=\"left\"|[[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]]\n|}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20090105120126/http://www.epo.gr/epag_prota/detail.asp?e_article_id=2074&e_article_cat_id=3 Hellenic Football Federation] {{in lang|el}}\n*[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesg/grkhist.html#63 Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]\n\n{{Super League Greece seasons}}\n{{1962\u201363 in Greek football}}\n{{1962\u201363 in European football (UEFA)}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1962-63 Alpha Ethniki}}\n[[Category:Alpha Ethniki seasons]]\n[[Category:1962\u201363 in European association football leagues|Greece]]\n[[Category:1962\u201363 in Greek football]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football league season\n| competition        = [[Alpha Ethniki]]\n| season             = 1962\u201363\n| winners            = [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]]<br/>3rd Greek title\n| relegated          = [[Prood